description: Created by Carl Potts. Written by Carl Potts and Chuck Dixon. Art by Larry Stroman. A handsome and hefty collection of Alien Legion's fantastic second series featuring scripts by Chuck Dixon and the charged pencils of Larry Stroman. Force Nomad is MIA - presumed dead - after a disastrous foray into the barren Hellscape of Quaal. Only Major Saringar holds hope that there are any survivors. Resigning his Legion commission, 'Citizen' Saringar sets off across galaxies to learn the true fates of Grimrod, Tamara, Montroc, Meico, and Zeerod.
name: Force Nomad

description: Created by Carl Potts. Written by Carl Potts and Chuck Dixon. Art by Larry Stroman. The spectacular follow-up to Alien Legion: Force Nomad, Piecemaker collects seven more issues in the Alien Legion saga. In stunning full color, Force Nomad resumes duty in a series of far-flung combat zones. The volatile Jugger Grimrod confronts his violent past, while Tamara faces a surprising future amid the always-perilous present that is the daily bread for Force Nomad of the Alien Legion.
name: Piecemaker

description: reated by Carl Potts. Written by Alan Zelenetz. Art by Frank Cirocco, Terry Austin, and Whilce Portacio. The third in a series of collections from Checker, showcasing the critically acclaimed comic book series created by Carl Potts, which ran from 1987 through 1991. Force Nomad is a galaxy-hopping band of mercenaries in the employ of the Alien Legion. They're a motley but effective fighting force, and always sent on missions that are just this side of suicide.
name: Footsloggers!

description: Just because Dame Darcy is busy with music, dollmaking, and being a reality TV star, that doesn't mean she's stopped baking her beloved Meat Cake, and here's a new issue to prove it! In Meat Cake #17, God is revealed to the Faeiry Sisters — so of course they get into a fight over it. Also, Trixxie Roxx stars in "The Horrors of Fame," what Darcy describes as "a punk-rock version of those cheesy 1940s romance novels where the girls are going through hyperdrama all the time" — plus more kee-razy neo-Goth fairy-tale madness from one of comics' true originals!

person_credits.name: Dame Darcy
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: Epic Graphic Novel: Last of the Dragons

description: The comic you can't wait to read to go along with the game you can't wait to play! The TRANSFORMERS: FALL OF CYBERTRON digital comic leads directly into the upcoming video game. Let Transformers: Robots in Disguise writer JOHN BARBER and hot new artist DHEERAJ VERMA introduce you to the world of Cybertron as we meet GRIMLOCK, SNARL, SLUG, SLUDGE, and SWOOP—the team that someday will be called—the DINOBOTS!
name: Good Intentions

description: Leading into the new hit game! Grimlock received a transmission from Swoop, who has discovered the source of the Decepticon's energon. Now learn what else Swoop found in the Sea of Rust! Written by JOHN BARBER and art by DHEERAJ VERMA, you won't want to miss this issue!
name: Secrets

description: Love TRANSFORMERS: FALL OF CYBERTRON the game? You don't want to miss the comic! Grimlock, Sludge, Slug, and Snarl move in to rescue Swoop from the Insecticons You'll want to check out JOHN BARBER's story and DHEERAJ VERMA's art as it takes you deeper into the world of FALL OF CYBERTRON!
name: Siege Mentality

description: The action doesn't stop, when Shockwave and the Insecticons intercept Grimlock, Sludge, Slug, Snarl, and Swoop, you experience the hardest hitting issue yet! Don't miss out on this issue of JOHN BARBER and DHEERAJ VERMA's saga!
name: Last Stand

description: The next chapter in this highly praised tale of life behind the iron curtain finds Jonas Finkel reaching his teen years. His father is still not to be seen and he and his mother are scraping by. Jonas, denied a good education, goes from menial job to menial job but then finds work in a bookstore. Government agents force Jonas to spy on the owner for them but he secretly rebels by joining a daring group of teens who read and collect forbidden literature. The group includes a girl with the most disturbing pair of blue eyes.
name: Adolescence
